==English==
===Etymology===
A derivitive word from [[garnish]]: from [[Germanic]] ''warnjan'' to guard: through Old French ''garnir'': to Middle English
===Noun===
'''garnishee'''
#{{law}} the person whose money is [[garnished]]
===Transitive verb===
'''to garnishee'''
#{{law}} the act of attaching the property sought to be secured.

